                                            patient call manager: the clinical call system™ 
                                            

patient call manager: the clinical call system™ 
Patient Call Manager: The Clinical Call System™, represents the next generation of systems designed to provide quality touch points along a patient’s continuum of care, both before and after you care for them within your four walls. This clinical call system is proven to increase patient safety, quality and experiences. 



                                            Provider Feedback System℠
                                            

Provider Feedback System℠
The Provider Feedback System℠ approach (PFS) combines our results-driven coaching with metric alignment software to improve clinical and operational performance for physicians. PFS fosters collaboration to meet the demands placed on successful healthcare organizations. It facilitates a partnership that is beneficial for all stakeholders and helps ensure that patients receive the best care in the most efficient way possible.



                                            validation matrix
                                            

validation matrix
The Validation Matrix is designed to automate and centralize the "always" execution of essential Evidence-Based LeadershipSM tactics for behaviors we know are linked to our ability to drive outcomes. As a component of the Leader Evaluation Manager® application or as a standalone product, the Validation Matrix is used to enhance the process of reviewing performance within the context of the Monthly Meeting Model.









Our Healthcare Customers' Markets


                            Academic Medical Centers
                            


                                            Academic Medical Centers
                                            

Academic Medical Centers
With the evolution of medical education and research, higher education funding shortfalls and massive industry transformation are creating unique challenges for academic medical centers (AMCs). Adding to these pressures is the perception that AMCs are more expensive – impacting consumer care selection and making payer negotiations challenging. Most at risk are AMCs that operate in urban areas and treat a high number of uninsured and Medicaid patients. Funding cuts for disproportionate share hospitals are rising at an alarming rate. 
These constraints make it difficult for AMCs to operate profitably. In response, many are designing and deploying new business strategies, consolidating, partnering with other local providers, diversifying their funding sources and curtailing operational costs. 
Navigating this journey can be daunting. That’s why Huron built an advisory team of former AMC leaders, higher education professionals and trusted strategists to help AMCs realize and maintain exceptional financial and operational performance. We leverage our depth of expertise and diversity of experience from working with 95 of the top 100 research universities to drive market-leading results. We work hand-in-hand with AMC leaders to deliver rapid, proven and sustainable outcomes. 





                            Community Hospitals
                            


                                            Community Hospitals
                                            

Community Hospitals
In today’s turbulent healthcare environment, community hospitals struggle to remain independent because of declining profit margins, changes in reimbursement models and reduced inpatient volumes. Whether fighting for their sovereignty or entering into strategic affiliations, hospitals must enhance value in every aspect of their operations. 
Together with the Studer Group, our advisors work with community hospitals to drive sustainable improvements. We work hand-in-hand with leaders at all levels to uncover insights, embed leadership, set new directions, reduce complexities and facilitate operational efficiencies. We also evaluate revenue cycle, clinical and support services as well as potential strategic partnerships to help community hospitals realize and maintain exceptional performance and organization-wide engagement.





                            Government Healthcare Organizations
                            


                                            Government Healthcare Organizations
                                            

Government Healthcare Organizations
Healthcare reform and shifting public policies are stressing our nation's city, county and state-run public health systems and institutions. Funding shortfalls, cuts to disproportionate share reimbursement, Medicaid program alterations and changing patient demographics also are overcrowding emergency departments, trauma centers and clinics.
At the federal level, organizations like the Veterans Health Administration, Department of Defense, and Indian Health Services are working diligently to optimize the quality of care they deliver. 
Navigating these challenges, while designing flexible and sustainable strategies with fewer resources, is no small task. Huron and Studer Group partner with various government health entities to optimize clinical and business operations and drive organization-wide engagement. Our team has extensive expertise in performance improvement, document and expense management, organizational change management review, formal risk management planning and executive and leadership coaching. Our unparalleled experience and flexible implementation plans can help public and government healthcare institutions realize and maintain exceptional performance as well as build a sustainable culture. 





                            Medical Groups
                            


                                            Medical Groups
                                            

Medical Groups
Medical groups are the “front door” to your health system and are often the critical first encounter that patients have with your healthcare system. For each inpatient visit, there are 20 visits to affiliated medical groups, which greatly strains operators and providers. Unlocking the potential of both employed and independent medical groups is critical for thriving in a value-based world. Together with Studer Group, we have a long, rich history of partnering with medical groups of all sizes to achieve sustainable change through improving operational performance and driving organization-wide engagement. 
As value-based care models increasingly link patient experience and clinical outcomes to reimbursement, health systems and affiliated medical groups need to improve quality of care scores on performance measures. Our transformation team has the strategic, operational and clinical experience to guide this transition. Our consulting and coaching capabilities create the accountability and change management strategies needed for long-term, sustainable success.
To learn more about our capabilities, visit our Medical Group Solutions page.





                            National and Regional Health Systems
                            


                                            National and Regional Health Systems
                                            

National and Regional Health Systems
Radical industry transformation is significantly impacting America’s national and regional health systems. Mergers, acquisitions and sell-offs are constant so the very composition of these systems, their value propositions and economies of scale and scope are ever changing. Additionally, the changes in regulations and laws impact how these systems deliver care and to whom, as well as how they are compensated. Specifically, national and regional health systems are grappling with different ways to:

Manage workforce planning and clinical operations
Integrate technologies to drive safer, efficient and more affordable healthcare
Improve both personalized and population health

To endure, many of today’s integrated delivery networks are consolidating, forging unprecedented partnerships, cutting costs and leveraging economies of scale – all of which can be difficult to achieve quickly or easily.
That’s where Huron and Studer Group come in. Our trusted strategic advisors help systems navigate these challenges by applying their depth of expertise and diversity of experience when and where it is needed most. We work hand-in-hand with health systems to facilitate lasting and sustainable improvements by creating strategies that are data-driven, analytics-enabled and experienced-based to realize and maintain exceptional performance.





                            Specialty Hospitals and Facilities
                            


                                            Specialty Hospitals and Facilities
                                            

Specialty Hospitals and Facilities
Major changes in reimbursement led by Medicare and Medicaid are challenging the delivery of care as well as the roles and structure of specialty hospitals and facilities. These institutions also face a shortfall of specialty providers, increased competition from emerging national and regional and national systems, cuts to vital research funding and decreasing revenue sources to offer preventive care. 
 Our partnerships with specialty hospital customers include:

 Behavioral hospitals
 Children's hospitals
 Cancer centers 
 Post-acute care providers and facilities
 Rehabilitation facilities
Surgical centers

Sustaining specialty hospitals and facilities requires a different way of thinking. It also requires deep expertise in clinical and operations management, revenue cycle optimization (particularly in states with Medicaid diagnosis-related groups) as well as managing resources based on fluctuating demand. With specialty care involving a variety of medically complex services, special attention also must be paid to the intricacies of the insurance verification processes. 
Huron’s record of success with specialty healthcare providers is unmatched. Our team of trusted advisors can help these entities improve operating performance, cultural knowledge and financial strength.  









