                            enterprise performance management
                            


                                            Overview
                                            

Overview
Huron specializes in partnering with our clients to deliver solutions that support the end-to-end enterprise performance management process, whether in the cloud or on-premise. With decades of solution delivery experience, we are able to offer our clients precise guidance based on their unique needs and requirements and deliver solutions that enable the finance organization to be successful at managing the business. From financial close, planning and forecasting, to risk and regulatory reporting, Huron’s strong finance and technical expertise with Oracle’s Enterprise Performance Management (EPM) and Oracle Financial Services Analytical Application (OFSAA) software solutions enable us to deliver meaningful change and sustainable results for our clients.



                                            Budget Planning and Forecasting
                                            

Budget Planning and Forecasting
Business planners need relevant, up-to-date and accurate data from various systems and implement (or redesign) solutions so that they can plan or forecast effectively and efficiently while adapting to changes in a scalable way.
Our team specializes in helping organizations understand, design and implement customized EPM solutions. We help organizations understand how to balance functionality and complexity while avoiding usability compromises for the business planning process. We deliver custom (driver-based and non-driver based) business planning solution components that are effective, efficient, scalable, adaptable and:

Ensure accuracy with a centralized, single-data repository that validates forecasts
Answer complicated strategic questions with a sophisticated analytical engine and optional drill-through technology
Reduce the time to deliver planning and forecasting results through automated processes and quick-to-implement modules
Optimize resource allocation strategies with customized algorithms and industry best practices
Align operational and strategic planning and forecasting efforts by leveraging hierarchical flows and structured procedures
Boost enterprise-wide adoption and collaboration with an easy to use Excel-like interface built for use by finance
Prevent data breaches using the latest security technology and methods
Support advanced modeling and enable 'what-if' scenario analysis




                                            Financial Close and Reporting
                                            

Financial Close and Reporting
Enterprise expansions, industry competition, and product/service re-engineering have made the financial consolidation and reporting efforts the single most important exercise a business will perform. To be competitive, you must find a faster way to close your books and report to both your internal and external stakeholders a clearer view of your business inside and out highlighting past, present and future performance. That is why, companies rely on our services for both our in-depth knowledge of today's hyper-competitive business landscape and the knowledge of the financial products available to support the key business decisions that drive quantifiable results and dramatically improve your company's close and reporting processes. 
From start to finish, we can help you optimize your solutions with flexible, transparent, and quick-to-implement solutions that include:

Integration of source system financial and non-financial information
Management of period-end close activities
Global accounting and standardized financial close solutions
Tax provision solutions
XBRL reporting offerings




                                            Profitability and Cost Management
                                            

Profitability and Cost Management
Profitability and cost management has become a critical component in the framework of enterprise performance management for helping to maximize the bottom line. Realizing the potential profitability and true costs of your products and/or services is necessary to improve performance - and helps with strategic decisions making and resource allocation (both financial and people).
Our solutions allow our clients to:

Align cost with revenue-based and key business drivers to achieve optimal profitability at each business segment (product, customer, channel, etc.)
Perform 'what-if' analysis to support decision-making during times of change, such as plant closure, reorganization, channel adjustments
Identify root causes and optimize flexibility and agility to maneuver within an ever complex market
Discover and analyze the true impact of Shared Services
Improve customer service and react to changing customer demands (price, product mix, packaging, capacity) with a clear understanding of the impact on profitability
Discover and comprehend the underlying drivers of the business, including creating drill-down capability




